text: just a psa as we start the new year. in regards to sexual assault, no means no. sleeping means no. no answer means no. absolutely, under any circumstance ever is it okay for a woman (or man) to wake up with someoneâ€™s hand up her (or his) shirt. that is sexual assault. regardless of whether every other time itâ€™s been yes, this is still sexual assault. replying â€œitâ€™s just a boobâ€ is not an appropriate response. we need to have more open dialogue about these very real issues that men and women deal with because change will never happen otherwise. iâ€™m sick and tired of worrying about being assaulted by strangers, but it hurts even more when itâ€™s someone you thought was a friend. please, please, please always communicate in these situations and raise awareness so that we can at least stop ignorant sexual assault. featuring a photo of me feeling like a badass to help alleviate my frustration. #metoo

on #newyearseve we wrote gaia's name in light up at her favourite pub (and ours) the square and compass in worth matravers. some impromptu #artforgaia courtesy of dom and maya.

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
this is to all the survivors of rape. i will not comply to the use of euphemisms. rape starts from that look on that man's face on that street that day to the many times your own boyfriend invited himself into your bed. we all deserve to treat our bodies like jewels - freely.
here's my piece of angst :
*why i don't drink at night*
*
his eyes are red of substance and hormones.
i do not fear him.
i despise him.
for making me the object of his unwanted desire.
for making me dirty.
*
i want to scratch myself out of my body.
peel myself like an orange.
wash my soul.
*
but i can't.
so i despise you.

text:
2018 has been a roller coaster ride for the oppressed and the oppressor, for the helpless and the powerful and for the campaigners and the bashers. from marital rape to homosexuality to #metoo we have come a long way. let us have a look at some of the most important events that india witnessed this year. 
#1 the tax is gone, now itâ€™s just the taboo

the sanitary pads were taxed at 12% under the gst which was launched in july 2017. the decision triggered protests, petitions and court cases that questioned why the government taxed pads as a luxury rather than an essential item, such as condoms, which are tax-free. last year, lawmaker sushmita dev launched a petition to demand a reduction or total removal of taxes on pads, citing that about 70% of the women in the country could not afford them. the government finally scrapped the controversial 12% gst on sanitary pads after a year-long opposition by campaigners. the health of your period is a basic human right, no one should pay for that. women shouldnâ€™t be taxed with something they are born with. the governmentâ€™s decision to exempt a basic hygiene product like the sanitary napkin from gst is a very big win for everyone across the country.

#2018rewind #highlights #women2018 #taxfreesanitarynapkins #gst #taboo #humanrights #womenite #sushmitadev #bleedfree #taxfreewings #notaluxury

text:
happy and sheroic 2019 from lon-art! last year we achieved more than ever and this was thanks to our amazing team, partners, sponsors and specially to you.
in 2019 we will focus in fighting back injustices and violence towards women through the arts, exhibitions, new museums tours and art workshops. 
hope you will join us!

don't let the patriarchy befall you in 2019!

2019 wishes: we want the museums full of women artists, more solo exhibitions by women artists, more women in the textbooks, and in power, more women marching and appreciating feminism and we want men to join us and fight back with us.

we also want to stop grieving women deaths, we want women to feel free and not fear when walking home alone, we want women to enjoy their bodies and sexuality to the full and don't feel ashamed. we want women not to suffer for being a woman. we want feminism for all, not matter what color, social class, sexuality or gender you belong to. 
#happynewyear #royalacademy #womenartists #womeninart #feminism #feminismforall #niunamenos #metoo #yotecreo #womeninart

text:
today i had two choices 1. to stay at home and throw my own pity party because i was alone on my birthday, or 2. go and do something i enjoy, and of course no. 2 was the go. i left home at 4.30 this morning and travelled up north, going to 12 beautiful waterfalls that i haven't been to yet. my absolute favourite was the karekare falls just south of piha absolute stunner, and i can't wait to take tara there. i also set myself a challenge as i managed to get to 20 waterfalls in 2018 since i got my little car, and because today i turned 27 my aim was to go to at least 7 different waterfalls, and i well and truly smashed that, so the count is now sitting at 32 waterfalls in the north island. in the past i would have sat at home and sulked, but because i've been making all these awesome positive changes in many aspects of my life, i am about creating my own happiness, it is not up to others to make me happy, i need to make my own happiness.
#nzsummer #zmsummer

today i had two choices 1. to stay at home and throw my own pity party because i was alone on my birthday, or 2. go and do something i enjoy, and of course no. 2 was the go. i left home at 4.30 this morning and travelled up north, going to 12 beautiful waterfalls that i have not been to yet. my absolute favourite was the karekare falls just south of piha absolute stunner, and i can not wait to take tara there. i also set myself a challenge as i managed to get to 20 waterfalls in 2018 since i got my little car, and because today i turned 27 my aim was to go to at least 7 different waterfalls, and i well and truly smashed that, so the count is now sitting at 32 waterfalls in the north island. in the past i would have sat at home and sulked, but because i have been making all these awesome positive changes in many aspects of my life, i am about creating my own happiness, it is not up to others to make me happy, i need to make my own happiness.
#nzsummer #zmsummer

text:
this may be a provoking post, but women really get bombarded on a daily basis with men on social media messaging them. i still do, i get many a week, sometimes many a day, both on my personal profile and via this page. generally it begins with an innocent 'hello' or 'how are you madame'... the energy reeks of predatory behaviour and you just know they are doing this to a lot of women online. it makes me cringe if i am honest.â €
â €
i have no idea where a certain group of men in the world believe that women want, need or invite this in.â €
â €
i used to know a woman who was naive when it came to this, she met him online and then she met the man overseas and he claimed he loved her, she had not become wise to this kind of thing, that he was using her for a passport into the country (not always the reason for contact of this kind).â €
â €
yes some men may be lonely, granted, but many women are too but don't message men online because we know it's just not the thing to do.â €
â €
when did it become okay?â €
â €
follow me on my blog, facebook or twitter or listen to my podcast on itunes (see bio for more info)â €
â €

text:
this might be trigering or disturbing for some individuals. read with caution. 
when writing this i embodied my experiences. i acknowledge the differences varied between sex, gender, race, access to health care and location etc. and i apologise. 
sexual assualt is a crime. sexual assault is defined as "sexual assault occurs when a person is forced, coerced or tricked into sexual acts against their will or without their consent,... sexual assault is a crime. sexual assault is not the victim's fault." as defined by the nsw government department of victims services. 
what if i have recently been sexually assaulted or a loved one has opened up about their assault?
the first thing to do is calm down and ask how long ago was the assault. getting yourself to a hospital asap.
((when i speak about the rest of the process i am speaking in a sense of australia /universal public health care. (if someone in the northern america dm about the process there i can pass it along to anyone who might need that resource).) step 1. go to the hospital. don't shower/change/or wash hands. bring a phone charger and headphones! 
step 2. present yourself to triage in the emergency room. the nurse will take your vitals and ask why you're in hospital. the hospitalis a safe place filled with professionals. nurses in emergency room are trained and qualified. i know you can be brave and tell the nurse that you have been sexually assaulted. the nurse will page the on call social worker and continue to ask you questions. such as: what happened in the situation, do you know the attacker/perpetrator, they will also ask if you think you've been drugged or suffered additional wounds e.g. cuts, scrapes, bruises, fractures and tearing. 
step 3: waiting. the on call social worker will be there as support and will link you to services. the social worker will ask you again to describe the situation so they can write a record for their services. 
continues in comments

text:
my mÃ£e and pai soon after they got engaged.

today i honour and give thanks to my mÃ£e and pai, as without them, i wouldnâ€™t be here today. i thank my parents for my portuguese/indian heritage it has brought me closer to understanding myself.

my parents divorced when i was five, it was a bitter divorce. my mÃ£e is my legacy, a beautiful soul and i will be indebted to her for the rest of my life. my pai loved his drink, gambling and women. he was brutal to my mum in front of me. his behaviour ripped our family apart. 
i am here in fatima on a solitude and reflection journey to heal the many broken pieces in my heart. i am here also to forgive the people who changed the course of my life as a child and wounded my soul and heart, my pai and my abuser. today i release both these men from all the pain and suffering they caused me as a child. 
i am letting go of all resentments and anger i have held. i am now free to embrace the new me, a totally freespirit risen from the ashes.

text:
#happykwanzaa #happynewyear
i chose my oldest daughters name based on the 7th principle of #kwanzaa "imani" is the substance of things hoped for without the evidence of being seen. #faith #imani 
as a teen mom,  without a living mother, i knew that i had to keep faith with me at all times.

in 5 weeks she will be 18 years old. she will be breaking multiple generational challenges. heading to graduation from high school with acceptance letters from the schools of her choice and honors! 
i'm so proud of her. i'm so blessed to have her in my life. she will be the 1st in her family (on her dads side to go to college & graduate). shes graduating high school without being a teen mom out of 4 generations (or more). i'm thankful for imani in my life. it hasnt been easy the past 18 years but she gives me hope for the future! 
#iamevidence #supremetransitions #endthebacklog #joyfulheart #blessed #detroitlove #everydayimok #metoo #issabeautifullife #healingispossible #freedom #selfcare #seasonschange #letsgohigher

text:
new class alert!! consent seems to be on everyoneâ€™s tongue with the #metoo movement and the continuous discourse in the public sphere. it is most often a conversation about sexual harassment and violence or within the context of romantic relationships and sexual encounters. leaving the discussion in the realm of sexual experiences (whether negative or positive) leaves out the importance of consent in our own bodies, families, and workplacesâ€¦ and the systems that created and reinforce perpetual consent violations. 
join touk keo (founder of the @radmeditationforbipoc and healer) and jess devries (sex and intimacy coach) to take a closer look at general consent including: - what is rape culture? - what conditions reinforce rape culture in individuals and american society as a whole? - when/how did we lose our personal agency? - how can we feel consent in our bodies? - how does being in trauma response affect our ability to give informed consent? - how does consent look different for the bipoc community and for the white community? 
this workshop will provide a framework for the cultural systems that we live in and how to connect with the knowledge of our bodies to help strengthen our personal agency. 
general information: 
date: saturday, january 26th
time: 2:00pm - 4:30pm
location: speec space - 5010 n commercial ave. portland, or 97211
accessibility: the speec space has two steps to enter and the bathroom is not currently ada accessible. it is close to trimet lines 44 and 72.
cost: $10-$30 sliding scale

space is limited. to reserve your spot please use the following link: paypal.me/jessdevries1

please dm with any questions regarding this workshop. 
#belovedcoaching #consent #divinerighttopleasure #endrapeculture #adultsexeducation #hireasexcoach

text:
i think it's important to revel in all of the amazing things i did in 2018, and also celebrate and learn from the failures. so here is a not comprehensive list of things i did in 2018:
- traveled solo internationally for the first time and was reminded of how much i find wonder in the world and how much i adore traveling alone. not surprisingly, many of my top 9 are from france.
- bought a brand new (!) car.
- continued to treat my body like a trash can. whoops.
- increased my credit score by 50 points, something i truly thought was impossible because of a path i was set on at 17.
- attended some truly phenomenal shows/readings/presentations, with highlights including hannah gadsby, the mcelboys, hank green, samantha irby with lindy west, and sally field.
- really struggled with all of the #metoo stuff, and especially christine blaisey ford's brave testimony.
- did a fairly good job taking care of myself with mental health days when needed as a result.
- got a new vibrator.
- read 130 books.
- failed to be there for friends (at least it felt that way) or flaked a few times.
- celebrated my 3-year anniversary at the 5th, the longest i've stayed in a professional job since i started working 10 years ago.
- cried a lot about the state of the world and especially the lack of empathy i see on a daily basis in our country.
- got a new prescription and new glasses for the first time in 8 years.
- still didn't date anyone because of my joy of being alone and dating is terrible and also childhood issues (see also "trash can body") but did have approximately 10 million crushes on all kinds of people.
- spent way too much time on social media.
- still lacked any semblance of patience.
- visited my bestie in new york where we did absolutely nothing and it was perfect.
- made some really good new friends.
- contemplated the meaning of life and humanity.
- nurtured a neighbourhood cat, bringing her from super skinny to a healthy weight. and fed some raccoons and possums in the process.
- said goodbye to my last grandparent.
- got my first christmas tree as a "grown up."
- had at least one existential crisis a week.
- turned 30! (finally.)

text:
today we talk about being a woman in any field ; be it medical, law, teaching , any profession , or even at home . #asawoman 
#asawoman , i love this picture because it is a selfie my three year old son took of his nanny, my housekeeper , him and me. this, right here is seemless parenting, that @indranooyiofficial talks about. i have taught my housekeeper every little nuance, from how to read childrenâ€™s books, revise his school poems and even cook for the house hold, such that it is seemless . today she has made prawn biryani for lunch and the spices are a bit much. i explained to her that for a chicken biryani the onions can be browned, the spices more vibrant, but for a delicate seafood like prawns the spices are milder. these simple and small tips, will make her cooking and mine almost seemless and identical. that would mean my family would not miss â€˜ma ke haath ka khaanaâ€™. many women will hold back what they know , but by giving my all, i support her . 
on the last day of work, a fellow colleague in the operation theatre wished me happy new year, and then added â€œ i wish you have another child this year.â€ #asawoman i would wish another female colleague , more success at work, that her paper get published, her presentation goes well, that she manage to get that great new machine for her practice, that she go on fabulous holidays and also pay off her emi. 
#asawoman i have been taught to ignore these male chauvinists, but i wish inhad replied with a â€œ same to you.â€ and see ya expression when a male doctor is wished he have another child this year, rather than professional success. 
#asawoman i donâ€™t expect less from myself, but i definitely expect more from others ; to step up. 
i read in the papers today that over 3,50,000 women in kerala formed a unique #womenswall across 620 km to support equality of gender , and a parallel â€˜solidarity wallâ€™ was formed by men in some parts of the state as well. letâ€™s form that wall #asawoman , even if itâ€™s on social media. 
this year , i hope to share how i manage my work, home, and everything in between #asawoman and support other women as they strike that balance. 
thankyou @nataliecrawfordmd , joining in from india .

text:
itâ€™s been on my mind a lot lately, about wishing i could say these words to a certain someone. 
to the complete stranger who showed me that there is still humanity in this world. i wish i could thank you. - today marks 2 years since my life drastically changed. for the better. that stranger was a part of that day. 
this personâ€™s voice is vivid in my mind. almost every time iâ€™m in my car alone and stop at a light i can still hear it so clearly. 
at the time i was assaulted, i was in the passenger seat of our car. we were stopped at a light when my ex was hitting me. i could hear someone from the car next to us yelling â€œwhat are you doing, what are you doing to herâ€. next thing i remember is our car swerving around. when i asked my ex why he was driving so fast he responded with â€œiâ€™m  trying to get away from the person tailing usâ€. although to this day i do not know if he attempted to notify police or how long he chased after our car or what he thought he would be able to do to help me.

but, the point is, there is someone out there who i wish i could make aware how thankful i am. thankful they saw something and wanted to try and actually do something for another human being they didnâ€™t even know. 
#thankyou #thrivingnotjustsurviving #domesticviolenceawareness

text:
dylan aka silly dilly mcwilly aka dyl-dyl crossed over the rainbow bridge on december 31st at 10:30am. 
a joker and a gentleman, he was a frisbee master, a gooser-greeter, a natural-born healer, a sock eater and chicken carcass stealer. he herded his kibble, compulsively made friends and helped me host years of parties. faster than the greyhounds at the dog park, dylan raced the wind and sometimes...he won. 
dylan reminded me to look for the happy. taught me how to live life in the present. made me smile with his snarfle-snort greetings. and helped me heal from my own #metoo with his unconditional love. he laid his head where he found hurting hearts and showed me how to really see the people around me. 
he spent his last christmas surrounded by family ... and stopped eating the next day. a trip to the vet confirmed what our hearts already knew. he was dying. two aggressive cancer clusters in his organs. 
we took him to the beach for his last two outings. he laid on a towel and enjoyed the smells until he decided to go for one last swim in the bay. and lickety split, the dog who hadnâ€™t walked for 3 days, took himself right down to the water and plonked in. i helped him paddle around until he decided it was enough. 
the vet came the next morning. snuggled up with us on the couch, he greeted the vet with a tired wag and sigh. listening to â€œover the rainbowâ€ by iz, we hugged and kissed him as he looked at us for the last time and exhaled. 
16 years of love. 
my best friend. 
a most beautiful soul. 
iâ€™ll always love you my precious boy. the world feels emptier without you.

ps...i hope the angels know how to throw frisbees! 
#ilovehimsomuch #adoptdontshop #bestwoof #myheart

text:
a few years ago i made the biggest change ever in my life by deciding to break free from a toxic relationship that was killing me physically, mentally, emotionally, and spiritually. since then,  i've had to adjust and survive as a single mother of three along with juggling day to day obstacles. but, i learned how to make it work and have been living a happier and healthier life since. now, i'm no stranger to overcoming challenges and leaving a toxic relationship was just one of the many struggles i've had to overcome. 
join on january 16 @ 7pm est for my free webinar where we will discuss the tools and resources i used to walk away from a toxic relationship, become a published author, and begin the journey to creating the life i always wanted. the first five people to sign up will receive a free copy of my book let mia tell it and everyone will receive my 30 day breaking toxic cycles journal for free! 
i can't wait to grow and elevate with you and assist you with breaking the cycles that has been holding you back and keeping you from living your best life! *select the linktree in my bio to sign up!!!! author/motivational speaker/blogger
mira cassidy

what is rape culture? rape culture is a set of cultural norms that are present in cultures that don't discourage rape. (they dont encourage rape, but sexual predators are not punished enough). there are a few things that are present in many rape cultures. 1. victim blaming. saying the victim is responsible. 2. saying "boys will be boys". this is one of the biggest problems. this ideology says that all boys do this, so why punish it? this is one of the reasons that rapists get such light punishment. 3. continuing to support rapists. this is very clear in hollywood, where people like louis c.k. are still given standing ovations despite being a predator. this also contributes to why some rapists have such light punishment. 4. catcalling and other forms of verbal harassment are said to be "just friendly" this isn't true.

text:
our society has come a long way in reducing the stigma around mental illness, but we still have a long way to go. many misconceptions and stereotypes relating to mental illness still exist.

so why does it matter? stigma can impact peopleâ€™s desire to seek treatment. stigma can cause those with mental health disorders to isolate themselves or develop negative thoughts and perceptions. it can also impact access to evidence-based treatment options.

we all can make an impact in our communities and society to reduce stigma. read on to learn more about how to reduce self-stigma and public stigma around mental health disorders. https://youwillbearwitness.com/2019/01/02/overcoming-stigma-associated-with-mental-illness/ #youwillbearwitness #metoo #ptsd #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #ptsdawareness #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #doitfordolly #trauma #therapydog #emdr #erinfado

text:
hello warrior women & all who support us!

i have started warrior women because i want all women to have a voice and to know a community of women exists to support, accept and love one another. below is a bit of my story and what has driven me to create warrior women on a mission.

when i was 13 years old i was sexually assaulted by a family member. six counts of sexual assault. i lost a lot by turning in my assailant. half of my family stood behind the adult assailant who had a prior history of similar actions. nearly every adult around me told me put what happened behind me and move forward, which was impossible. i was lost and i trusted the wrong people. one even told me i should kill myself because i was worthless. going through all of this was made even more difficult by the people in my household. my mother has always been self involved (and addicted to something my whole life) and my step-father never liked me (he literally would get angry if i accidentally walked down the hallway at the same time he did). both were physically and emotionally abusive at different times of my like. i often felt i did not belong anywhere.

by the grace of god, strong adult influences, a few family members and friends (who are my  family) i survived and made it to adulthood. however, just because i turned 18 and could move out (which i did the day i turned 18) i was not ok, not even close (to see more of the story, please go to the warrior women on a mission facebook page). while going through all of this i realized the most crippling feeling is shame. i really evaluated why i felt shame and a few things came upâ€¦the silence. i often stay silent because i am afraid of what people will think when they find out. the lack of education leads to a variety of reactionsâ€¦some are silent and some have said â€œohâ€. the worst reaction was when someone said i did not need to know that, i cannot help you. well, i have decided i want to educate everyone possible! i want to build a community of support for any woman who need to be reminded of the warrior she is! thank you for reading my story and for supporting warrior women on a mission! #warriorwomenmission #wwmaz #metoo

text:
so many
different dreary worlds,
that itâ€™s hard to make a choice,
hard to choose at all,
hard to have to.

ahh, thatâ€™s it isnâ€™t it? choice.
the great commanding curse
of freedom. itâ€™s very source.

no freedom without it,
only a painful apathy,
with no worry, and no hope.

for hope is always tight with worry,
hope and dread, did i make the right choice?
did i choose wrongly? the stress, anxiety
over the future, over itâ€™s hope.

yet, and still, there are no wrong choices,
just fleeting, frozen moments.
forever, and without changes,
with no way to make them.

so donâ€™t worry,
just choose and go, follow
freedomâ€™s path to the next choice,
and donâ€™t worry,
enjoy the hope.

sandra osborne

text:
as we step foot into the new year i canâ€™t wait to see what 2019 has in store for me as a new mother, lover and daughter of god and my family.ğŸ’• in early 2018 i closed a dreadful chapter of my life. many people donâ€™t know that i am a survivor of sexual assault. two years ago i wouldnâ€™t have even thought about saying it out loud in an empty room. and for the past two years i faced many struggles that challenged my education, my physical and mental health, friendships and personal relationships. it wasnâ€™t easy, especially in the mist of #metoo headlines that faded into thin air the moment the next trending topic came along. ever week showcased a new survivor and every week we forgot about the last. i felt like a stranger in my own skin and felt zero relatedness to any of them.

soon as my case came to a close, i said #enough to many of my toxic traits, people and habits. i learned to trust my soul and listen to the rhythm of my heart beat. i took to god many of my worries and pain. in return i was blessed with two of the most beautiful miracles. 
ryan and our baby. 
the most beautiful blessings to set foot in my life and heart. itâ€™s been a year full of awakening moments. some challenging. but most of them joyful! through all the hardships, ryan stood by my side and together weâ€™ve worked a foundation based on love, respect and mutual support. forever my love bug. ğŸ˜˜

2018 taught me to speak up for myselfğŸ—£. live in the momentğŸ§˜ğŸ½â€â™€ï¸. love unconditionallyâ¤ï¸. take risks. challenge my career through different avenues. budget my lifestyle and make better financial decisions. i learned to trust in godâ€™s word and make a life surrounded by like minded peopleâœ¨. in 2018 i laughed. i cried. i felt pain, i felt helpless. i felt vulnerable. i felt joy. i felt love. i felt fear at the sight of almost miscarrying. i experienced the first movements of my baby swimming in my womb. felt my babyâ€™s first kicksğŸ‘£. i walked the stage accompanied by my two sisters ğŸ‘¯. i received my bachelors degreeğŸ‘©ğŸ»â€ğŸ“. i bought my first car. landed my first full-time job as a college graduate. put up our first christmas tree in our new place and spent the new year cuddled in bed sound asleep. ğŸŒ™

happy new year! something that's always been apart of my life is bodies of water. oceans, lakes, ponds, rivers, creeks. water has the capacity to destroy and provide. i almost drowned when i was 5. yet, i spent nearly every summer from 7-18 swimming in a river. i can heal from that accident and go onto love something i was afraid of. i had to make changes and face my anxiety about the water hurting me again. it's no different than other parts of my life. accidents happen and i will get hurt (most often times emotionally). that's a part of life, and it's hard to accept when things change. it's been even harder to do so because a lot of the changes in my life weren't from decisions i made. one of my resolutions is to stop white-knuckling life. if i spend so much time anxious about the past repeating itself, then i'm going to miss out on opportunities to make positive change in my life. ğ˜'ğ˜·ğ˜¦ ğ˜£ğ˜¦ğ˜¦ğ˜¯ ğ˜¥ğ˜°ğ˜ªğ˜¯ğ˜¨ ğ˜µğ˜©ğ˜ªğ˜´ ğ˜§ğ˜°ğ˜³ ğ˜ºğ˜¦ğ˜¢ğ˜³ğ˜´ ğ˜¯ğ˜°ğ˜¸, ğ˜´ğ˜° ğ˜'ğ˜® ğ˜¯ğ˜°ğ˜µ ğ˜¦ğ˜¹ğ˜±ğ˜¦ğ˜¤ğ˜µğ˜ªğ˜¯ğ˜¨ ğ˜ªğ˜µ ğ˜µğ˜° ğ˜¨ğ˜° ğ˜¢ğ˜¸ğ˜¢ğ˜º ğ˜´ğ˜°ğ˜°ğ˜¯. however, i'm finding small steps to take to feel more safe in the world without relying on avoidance. both my art and what i do with my spare time will reflect this. i'm working towards healing and i will have raging tides as well as still waters. i can have both and still be making progress.

my story pt.2
my younger cousins noticed that i had a huge red stain on my pants and started asking me if it was juice or if i cut myself really badly or if i was in pain. i forgot to mention that they always said that if i say no that they will cry and that they felt physical pain and said that if i said anything about it that their mom will punish them(i'm black so an ass whopping is something that everyone feared). i always said no even though i know that the older ones have been touching me and using me for pleasure. when my mother for home the younger ones told her and she drove me to the hospital and brought me to the emergency room. on the way there i wasn't allowed to sit down. i remember the doctor asking me the same questions that my younger cousins and mother asked me. i denied all of them and moved on  with my life. few years prior to the incidents my mom showed me a video about consent, sex and rape. after that everything became clearer to me. the night she showed me the video i told her about my cousins and she took me to therapy from our pastor's wife. it didn't really help because they would openly talk about my situation during church. my mom left the church after it ruined her marriage, embarrassed me  and stole money from her. last year at my old school boys would touch my but and breast and trigger me giving me flash backs and i didn't trust any guys at school. to anyone reading rape  is not the victim's fault. no means no. drunk and unable to reply means no. change of thought means no. this really needs to stop. what the victim is wearing should not matter. it's the men and women who rapes people who should be looked at not the victims. if you are going through anything please tell someone it might make you feel better. dm if you want to rant or talkğŸ’–

text:
the transition from 2018 to 2019 was like a slow motion trainwreck for me. ğŸ™ˆ
.
2018 threw some major curveballs my way with scant recovery time in between: my first major surgery, the uncovering of abuse and scandal within a religious group that was a huge part of my formative early adult years, and the sudden death of one of my best friends.
.
even without these life stressors, 2018 would have been challenging enough. itâ€™s only been 3 years since i left my abuser, and my recovery still requires what feels like all of my energy and intention.
.
losing jill so tragicallyâ€”at the hands of the mental health providers who were supposed to be helping herâ€” has sent me into a spiral of grief and anxiety that couldnâ€™t neatly be laid to rest at the end of 2018. it feels wild and important and scary and devastating. this new trauma has rubbed against the shrapnel already in my system, and my c-ptsd symptoms have reared their ugly head again. iâ€™m stable right now but know i need to pursue extra treatment and support at the onset of 2019 to better manage my triggers. i want to integrate and heal. âœ¨
.
i know by experience that life goes on, even after loss and trauma and death. integration is possibleâ€”the commingling of joy and suffering. acceptance is the gateway. but itâ€™s hard work.
.
i acknowledge that 2018 brought many joys with it along with my these hardships, but i will save those gratitudes for another post. right now, itâ€™s important for me to publicly express my grief as i process jillâ€™s death and how this loss has shaken me to my core. ğŸ’”
.
i want this first post of the year to be blatantly honest about my mental health struggles right now, and i hope it encourages all of you who are also struggling this winter. the pressure to be optimistic at the start of a new year isnâ€™t always helpful and can feel isolating if youâ€™re just trying to get through the day. be gentle with yourself and know you arenâ€™t the only one thinking â€œgood riddance, 2018. what a dumpster fire of a year.â€

text:
have you seen that video of the first 2019 baby born at the guatemalan hospital? no way am i sharing that *tw - if you havenâ€™t seen it, be mindful about investing your energy there. i caught it unaware and itâ€™s traumatic. my purpose in discussing it here is because i know many will have seen it and are now reeling from their emotional, bodily and soul reaction to it

so letâ€™s talk groupthink and vicarious trauma 
when you get a hungry pack of adrenalin fuelled egos together, people lose touch with their values and themselves. they get swept up in the group pull to achieve an outcome. the brain narrows its focus to a mere pinprick of detail and nothing else matters except the win. in this case, getting the first photo of the first 2019 baby

itâ€™s now emblazoned in my mind as flashbulb memory. yet another piece of cultural narrative showing humans at their worst that i have to explain to my daughters one day. like a picture of a child running down the street, naked, covered in napalm

to me, the look on that mamaâ€™s face was one of learned helplessness. defeat. horror. pain, distress and complete dismissal of human rights as a room full of people took full advantage to party and capture the moment 
this is what an absence of informed consent looks like. this is what groupthink looks like. the stanford prison experiment. the milgram experiment. when you know thereâ€™s a voice inside just one person screaming â€œthis isnâ€™t rightâ€. but they go along with it. itâ€™s cult behaviour 
how is it any different to the glorification of sexual violence with selfies? 
my tolerance for trauma is freakishly high. it has to be. working with the sights, sounds, smells and out of body experiences of trauma is what i do

yet i am grieving and devastated for this mama and her baby. for all the people who will watch this video and add it to their collective consciousness about who  has the power in the birth space 
#birthtrauma #ptsd #vicarioustrauma #birthworker #secondarytrauma #metoo #endobstetricviolence #birthrights 
@birthmonopoly @birthwithoutfear @the_angela_gallo

text:
happy new year!

2019 has just begun and we already have projects lined up. one, filming next week, is our next micro-short in the life improvised series, capturing the small moments that make up life, love, relationships.

this one is called xchange and deals with a powerful woman and her encounter with an escort. we're excited to finally be working with vanessa de largie in the lead role.

vanessa de largie has been the resident sex columnist at maxim magazine since february 2017. 
she's an award-winning actress and author.Â  she's also a prolific journalist and social commentator.

vanessa's work primarily focuses on fierce female sexuality and gender politics. 
her feature articles regularly appear in the spectator, the daily telegraph, the huff post and penthouse magazine.

www.vanessadelargie.net

we're also reuniting with @frankfazio
from @in_corpore_film to complete the cast and @gerardmackfilmcomposer
and stephen ramplin from @friendsfoesfireworks on crew. it's a melbourne reunion and we can't wait to film!

#lifeimprovised #nexusproductiongroup #microshorts #relationshipdrama #xchange #improvisedfilm #improvacting #melbourne #writer #sexlife #actor #acting #sexcolumnist #melbourneactor #metoo #timesup #womenwholead

text:
as i reflect over the past year (hell, the past few years) and what 2018 has brought me, i've learned to never discount your support system, ones who will circle the wagons for you. no matter if it be one or twenty-one... it's about the depth of commitment to each other not the numbers in your wagon circle. i often think about the hardships the pioneers must've endured but also the joys of knowing at the end of the day they had each other... i can only imagine the stories that were told around the campfires at night.. ** circle the wagons

wagon trains crossing the plains parked their wagons in a tight circle at night for two reasons. the circle was a somewhat defensible, makeshift fort, in case the company came under attack. and it formed a sort of corral, to keep cattle and other livestock from scattering. **
i'm grateful to those who:
-helped me through panic attacks, coming to my aid when i reluctantly called for help. -gave me a kick in the ass when i was being unreasonable and hard headed
-loved me when i was unlovable.
-sat with me in silence because that was what i needed at that moment.
-inspired me to be a better mom.
-traveled with me and listened to me drone on and on about who knows what.
-gave me distractions -let me be there for you when you needed my support.
-encouraged me to create more art
-gave me cuddles
**
i can't say that 2019 will be my year or the best year yet.. all i can say is i now have hope. i have the hope that i will continue to heal, to grow, to love, to live, to survive and work towards thriving. and when it comes time to circle my wagons may i have the foresight to do so and may we weather the storm or difficulty or attack together with strength, love, understanding and grace.

text:
i took break from social media while ago because of my depression and becuase of other horrible events in my life. and that break helped me a lot. in that period, i gave time to myself. i processed my thoughts and just healed. i thought i won't be able to stay without instagram and snapchat and other apps because i was so addicted to it but it felt better to just take a break from it and stay with myself. i figured lots of things during the break. i came back as a different person and also i started this account thinking that i might help few people you know. i am proud i did that. so if necessary take a break, it is completely okay.

text:
dear 2018,

thank you. thank you for the man that nearly tore me in two. thank you for the love that pushed me to reach for me so that in the aftermath i stand strong in: i am. thank you for the new home, the old one, and the sisters who held my heart when i couldnâ€™t cry anymore. thank you for the lovers and the haters, thank you for the stories on stage and the stories shared. thank you for two new nieces and one lost grandmother. thank you for the process of shedding identity so i am more authentically me, brilliant and bright, regardless of what they see. thank you for me. thank you security. thank you for lore. thank you for the many women who graced the @empowerhertoday stage - i will never be the same - the listeners will never be the same - our city will never be the same. thank you for #metoo. thank you for the rallies and the sacred circles. thank you for wise women who reminded me that i am wild. thank you for strong men who stood beside me and bared their souls. thank you for poetry and prose. thank you for loss. thank you for hozier and sweden. thank you for detroit and ann arbor and louisville and chicago and pittsburgh and new york city and raleigh and florence and lake cumberland and cincinnati and copenhagen. thank you for baseball and basketball and football and track and ballroom dancing. thank you for @aileron_org and dayton entrepreneurs. thank you for @levittdayton and the i love you mural (@tiffanyallynartist ) and @thebrightsidedayton and dayton culture works and @updayton and dayton history fight night and this city. thank you for riverscape and flying pizza and the steelers in cincinnati and 2.0 and chillicothe and ludlow falls. thank you for #themoth and @truetheatre and @doubleedged and @pkdayton and #storyslamdayton and @daytonpoetryslam and @sparkfairborn and @bigbigstoryconsulting and @nucleusdayton . thank you for the miles on my car. thank you for the dollars in the bank. thank you for my red heels. thank you for my health. thank you for my family. thank you for my friends. thank you for my growth. thank you.

sincerely,
2019

today was one of the most awful new yearâ€™s days iâ€™ve ever had. so i got to thinkingâ€”i obsessively listen to â€œwelcome to the black paradeâ€ by @my.chemicalromance ; itâ€™s about sacrifice, suffering, and continuing on. 
i am tired of being victimized for painting nudes, and i viewed rembrandtâ€™s self portraits yesterday. so, i thought, in this #metoo era, why not use my body as a canvas and adhere myself? here is the result. the paint body blue & red stripes represent the ones in the @my.chemicalromance black parade video. i hope you like it.  i love you all, instagram peopleâ€”what would i do without you?! #canvaspainting #mychemicalromance #art#arte#kunst

text:
hey family! first project of the year is a one act that i will be directing and it's a doozy!!!! #theassaults is written by marilynn anselmi and stars kirrin tubo and lena enck at the secret theatre in long island city, queens.
synopsis: shel talks tonya into reporting an on-campus sexual assault to the newly formed women's center director. the reveal of the alleged prepetrator forces the director to face her own personal choices. 
opening thursday jan 3rd at 7:30pm, the show also runs saturday, january 5th at 3pm and friday, january 11th at 8pm. tickets are 20.00 and there is a concession stand with wine and snacks. you can purchase your tix online or at the door. link in my bio! 
and our play is under the aea showcase code, so equity folks feel free to come out and support! you will be seated once all paid attendees are in. audience votes will get us into the finals to compete for awards and prizes! hope to see you there!!! #secrettheatre #metoo #indietheatre #ourstoriesmatter #aea #unionactor #idirect #iproduce #iact #actors #blacktressmagic #offoffbroadway #wayoffbroadway lol

text:
intimacy.

this is my word, prayer, intention, for 2019.

last year was â€œrememberâ€. and looking back i can see the power of this prayer by its unique, yet deep simplicity.

so, i want to share with you something very personal and intimate that happened and that only my close friends know about.

as i set this intention in january 2018, i was going to embark on a long sexual trauma practitioner training and tantric exploration.

the remembering came in june 2018, when during a training and practice session i discovered (i remembered) that i was sexually abused by a few men when i was a child #metoo.

the trauma memory was in the depth of my body, hidden from my conscious mind. needless to say, that the experience was very intense and yet i discovered, in the horror of the trauma, the blessing it brought for my path and my calling.

it allowed me to finally understand so many of my behaviors, from my fear (and anger) towards powerful & strong men, to my capacity to feel an infinite depth of empathy for sexually abused people.

i also felt immense gratitude for the close friends who showed up during that time to hold me and realized how essential it was/is in my healing process (as it is for all trauma victims). i felt also that the past 15 years of deep spiritual work, allowed me to be able to hold my trauma in a container of light, of love, and of deep tenderness.
.
so this year my word is intimacy.
.
intimacy with...
.
(end of post in my blog, link in instagram bio profile)
. â¤ï¸

text:
my tiny drawing of the essence of woman.
this woman is appreciated and trusted for her love, gentleness, nurturing and compassion.
she carries age-old wisdom and intuition with her as part of her being to help to balance our out-of-kilter world.
she takes no power away from men but seeks to add hers to theirs - to be complimentary. there's no reason to worry or fear.

she's never been abused: emotionally or physically. never has she been vilified in society for demanding equality; never ridiculed because of her bodily functions; never had her life-choices dictated by powerful old white men; never disparaged for demanding justice; never denied freedom of choice because of her gender.
never demonized.

never sexually abused as a child, never silenced by her partner by beating; never raped; never had to try to heal her child after a sexual predator has attacked; never disrespected just because she is female.

text:
january 1, 2019
itâ€™s a perfectly magical, quiet and snowy day for introspection. 
i honestly didnâ€™t know if i was going to make it to today. 
there were so many days last year, mostly in the first half, where i just fought to make it to the end of the day without daydreaming of all the ways that i could put a permanent end to my pain. 
i didnâ€™t know if i would make it to a day where all of my thoughts were not directed towards pushing though the fire and fog of pain and weakness; and trying not to injure myself further- intentionally or not. 
i discovered a new love for sunsets.
they were a bright and brilliant reminder that i had made it to the end of another day; that there was still beauty and magic and wonder despite feeling like life was shrouded in unchangeable darkness. 
i was living in the worst of the what ifs:
what if my life is always life this?
what if i become worse and end up permanently disabled? how will i work and provide for myself? 
what if no one else can handle this and i have to deal with this alone for the rest of my life?

and worse
what if i become a person i donâ€™t recognize- will i let pain and inability make me bitter, angry, and joyless? 
what if i become a burden on everyone i know and no one can stand me?
what if i let this defeat me and end it for good?  how much pain would my family be in?  how could i hurt them like that?

every day i had to choose to fight for a life and future hope that i could not yet see. 
as i am looking back on this year, i see the hardships and what all i lost, i would never want to repeat it, but as i am coming out on the other side- still struggling forward, but now with hope; i see that i have learned to fight for myself like never before. 
i have learned the ability to look for and hold onto the good- in every situation.
i have learned that i donâ€™t always have to be the strong one.
i have learned to let people into my true reality- weakness, ugliness and all; but understand that i am the only one who can carry it all the time. other people have their own shit to deal with and my pain does not stop the world from turning. ha!
i have learned a patient strength...

text:
via @audreaming2 "my tiny drawing of the essence of woman.
this woman is appreciated and trusted for her love, gentleness, nurturing and compassion.
she carries age-old wisdom and intuition with her as part of her being to help to balance our out-of-kilter world.
she takes no power away from men but seeks to add hers to theirs - to be complimentary. there's no reason to worry or fear.

she's never been abused - emotionally or physically. never has she been vilified in society for demanding equality; never ridiculed because of her bodily functions; never had her life-choices dictated by powerful old white men; never disparaged for demanding justice; never denied freedom of choice because of her gender.
never demonized.

never sexually abused as a child, never silenced by her partner by beating; never raped; never had to try to heal her child after a sexual predator has attacked; never disrespected just because she is female. "

text:
this new years eve rather than partying and making resolutions i donâ€™t intend to keep, i reflected. a lot. with that reflection came a lot of tears. my entire life i made decisions based on how it would benefit other people. itâ€™s all i have known. 
you see, i was born a light into a world of chaos. so from very early on i used my gift of bringing love and light to so many others even when it meant sacrificing my own needs. over the years though i became tired. really fucking tired. which is why i decided to change.

i have experienced some of the darkest pains. i have endured trauma, alone. more times than i could count. and while it made me hard in the sense that i didnâ€™t let people all the way in. i never stopped sharing the love i have inside of me. because i truly want you to be happy. i want you to feel loved. 
death. divorce. verbal abuse. rape. molestation. emotional and physical abuse. multiple suicide attempts. abandonment. betrayal. and so much more. yet i still love. i love so fucking hard and i always will. do you know why? because that is what i choose. i choose love. you can too. 
happy new year. sending you so much love and light. ğŸ’› #chooselove #love #light #happynewyear #2019 #metoo #iamchristinefrancis

text: we are researching for a new blog in 2019. this passage from the second sex (de beauvoir, 1949) is the passage that debunks freudâ€™s theories of female penis envy. a theory postulated in the 1800s, debunked in the 1940s is experiencing a resurgence in the 2010s because of some psychologist (jordan peterson) who is trying to make psychology great again (it wonâ€™t be great again until the dsm is broken down and re-written, and if you donâ€™t know what that is, donâ€™t talk to me about jordan peterson). according to de beauvoir and her contemporaries, women are not traumatised by or envious of the phallus, unless you give them cause. to a â€œwomanâ€ (cis or trans) this seems so simple, almost logical even, because it explains a womanâ€™s anger. post #metoo there is a new push to whip men into shape, to redefine masculinity. however it is no longer helpful to define masculinity in an specific way... because it simply doesnâ€™t exist. you can be strong when you need to be, you can be vulnerable when you need to be... these traits are not gendered, they are present in all humans, the moment you attribute gender to them, is where the toxicity begins. disabusing young men and women of their gendered upbringing is a hard task, but we all go through it in the end as we grow up and self-actualise. those who cling to societal constructs are those that are disillusioned in the end. this man is trying to make men less â€œtoxicâ€ by re-assigning gender to men who are confused and angry about feminism and their place in the world. however this is only a bandaid on a much larger problem that does not effect young men alone. ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~#penisenvy #femalesexuality #malesexuality #metoo #simonedebeauvoir #cleanyourpenis #jordanpeterson #gender #poststructuralism #queertheory #judithbutler #dick #penis #vagina
name: Mary-Jane Ward

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied. 
in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking â€˜ugh. totally uglyâ€™ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
10:30am in anchorage, alaska and a tangerine pink powder puff sunrise suspended moment is not to be missed! but, it happens. everyday, we turn. the sun appears to rise and we are (briefly) illuminated. itâ€™s in those moments of transition where the most fleeting, spectacular, sensational, jaw dropping, conversation stopping dance of light and dark and color and shape and emotion often arise! 
how can we translate the beauty and grace of our planetâ€™s pirouette into the rhythms of our own life?
can we pause and gaze with gratitude at the beauty before us? what transitions are unfolding before you? 
has someone just arrived or left? are you breaking up? getting together? starting something? finishing up? is it messy? are you a bit unsure? 
we all are. 
take refuge in your own loving heart, help it grow stronger and more accessible by listening closely to its call, by putting yourself in the presence of kind and generous people, by letting yourself love whatever it is that you do. even if, especially when, itâ€™s not the easy thing to do. sometimes itâ€™s saying no to the celebration so you can stay home and pet your dog... and weep. 
may you know the beauty that you are. may you be guided by grace and may all of the colors appear in your rainbow...
wishing you, wishing always, for peace and so grateful for joy!! may 2019 carry us with care. 
resolved? me too. 
iâ€™m offering a little intro to meditation series in anchorage before our winter retreat. wednesday, 1/2, 5:30-6pm. check calendar (link to website in bio) for more details or dm me! 
thank you for your practice - and delight in all of the ways that it appears! ğŸ™ğŸ¼ #resolved #2019 #solsticelight #winter #alaska #anchorage #yogateacher #meditation #meditationteacher #alaskayoga #sunrise #practice #thisisyoga #metoo

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
"may we never meat again"
the hindu businessline, 28.12.18
by anita roy:
"looking back at 2018, it seems like this year has been a tipping point of sorts. not so much #metoo butÂ #meat?oo! "vegans have come out of the woods, and staked a claim to the mainstream. "supermarket shelves are stocked with vegan products â€” some now have whole aisles dedicated to plant-based, meat-free, dairy-free, cruelty-free products. theyâ€™re not free â€” but, as with organic foods, the slow and steady upsurge in popularity for vegan products is beginning to bring prices down. "what has driven this turn away from meat? the headline forÂ the guardianâ€™s environment editor damian carringtonâ€™s article published in may sums it up in a nutshell: â€œavoiding meat and dairy is the â€˜single biggest wayâ€™ to reduce your impact on earth.â€ "he references a study published in the journalÂ scienceÂ and co-authored by oxford academician joseph poore, which begins with a stark fact: â€œwith current diets and production practices, feeding 7.6 billion people is degrading terrestrial and aquatic ecosystems, depleting water resources, and driving climate change.â€ "if that wasnâ€™t enough to put you off your tandoori chicken, there are also the rising fears of what pesticides and chemical fertilisers, not to mention gm crops, are doing to our food, as well as the additional horror of how plastics have now entered the food chain and are ending up clogging our internal systems just as much as our external ones. "thereâ€™s also an increasing reluctance to see fellow sentient beings â€” cows, pigs, chickens, mainly â€” as simply â€˜raw materialâ€™ fed into one end of the agro-industry and squirted out at the other on to our dinner plates."

text:
beethoven sonata 30, opus 109 no. 1
â€”
by the timeÂ beethovenÂ composed this work, his output had declined substantially, perhaps owing to his deafness and disappointments in life. the only complete works to emerge from the period of 1820-1823 were the last three piano sonatas, the missa solemnis and the ninth symphony. even when compared to these imposing works, the e major piano sonata retains its status of a masterpiece. it is a remarkable work in several respects. Â·
the first movement has a nearly unique structure: it opens with theme marked vivace ma non troppo that almost immediately slows to an adagio espressivo. thereafter, the two contrasting tempos and utterances alternate. scarlatti andÂ mozartÂ had used such a scheme before, but never in such a bold and innovative fashion. on the surface, this short movement has a serene, almost angelic quality, but, like many other works written during this period, the composition's surface is merely one dimension among many. indeed, nothing about this sonata is one-dimensional. thus, for example, the subdued, brightly lit realm suggested by the beginning of the works eventually leads the listener to sections where the narrative slows down, conjuring up dark shadows that intimate feelings of longing and doubt.
.
.
.
.

text:
from 11/08 to december 2010 i was in inpatient treatment for the childhood trauma i went through. sometimes i forget what it was all like. sometimes i forget that i was abused at the hands of one of the people i fully trusted, someone who was supposed to be helping me. 
my 6th program. 
three 5150â€™s, 
19 fucking weeks in a full on wilderness program where i was sexually assaulted and then accused of rape by the same person. no investigation was ever done. i was a problem. a sexual deviant who couldnâ€™t be helped.  and after they sucked as much money out of my family as they possibly could, they told me i was nowhere near ready to go home and told my parents i needed to go to a boarding school. 
i was then sent to a therapeutic boarding school where i was victimized an innumerable number of times by a disgusting man who groomed me for months till i trusted him more than my parents, and then used it all against me for his sexual gain. i wanted any way out, and i ended up in the hospital after i fully tore open a surgical incision from a routine hernia repair i was recovering from. i couldnâ€™t take the abuse any longer, i was in the hospital when i finally confided in my mother about what was happening to me everyday. the individual was arrested the next day. and before i knew it i was on my way to another program. i was 15 years old, and i had given up completely. i was tired. i felt like i had no way out. and once again i was put another program. 
i was fully checked out before i had even been checked in. 
my therapist and many others went out of their way to save me from myself. someone got through to me. something finally clicked. i started opening up. i started working the program. re-engaging in my life. they helped me more than i could ever repay. they handed the life i had given up on back to me.  i just found my personalized yearbook that was made for me right before i went home. i sat and cried for a good hour staring at these photos. remembering everything iâ€™ve survived, and how strong i know i am. itâ€™s time to dust myself off and keep on trucking. i canâ€™t beat myself up over things i never had control over. ğŸ’• 
itâ€™s time to be my own hero! ğŸ¦¸â€â™€ï¸ #metoo

text:
discussion / feminity

i feel like as a man, for a long time in my life i did not realized the inequality that face women. inequalities and issues such as double standard, salary gap, rape culture, slut shaming.. i was never scared of walking at night. i never looked behind me to verify if i was being followed. i was never scared of being kidnapped and sold as a sex slave or an escort in the other coast of the country. i was never scared of some kind of "revenge porn" happening to me.

people that i know were actually victims of situation like those. kidnapping. drugging. rape. leaked nudes. groping in public places. its something real and then people are talking about an "already achieved equality of the sexes". dont you let them fool you. where i come from we still judge a girl by the tightness of her skirt and by what she decides to show on her ig account.

i find social medias are not helping that situation where theres hyper sexualization of women. too much pictures that portray women as what seems of a sexual object, an item, a crude article. how can it help women's situation if it places them as individuals good for nothing but taking ass pics? those disproportionate bodies, exaggerated lips, impossible hips sre quickly becoming the "norm", standard silhouettes.

women are more than bodies. women are more than ig models. women shouldnt be scared of walking at night and be the victims of constant fear of men. they shouldnt have old men politicians deciding laws for their bodies. they should decide for themselves. they are your moms. your daughters. your wives. cherish them.

text:
on the 31st of december on new yearâ€™s eve, when most were out celebrating the new year or getting ready to, over 100 members of the muslim community, young and old, of central london attended the annual qiyam at a local masjid.

the first speaker addressed the difficult questions muslims have to face on a daily basis. the speaker addressed two such questions, â€˜women in islam oppressed?â€™ and â€˜fitting inâ€™. the speaker addressed both in showing we have nothing to hide or be shameful about and rather we should show how women in the west are treated and put the onus back on them (#metoo). the speaker touched on how muslims should be proud of islam and being muslims and never feel the need to fit in and dilute their values and beliefs. the speaker ended with an inspirational reminder from the life of the companion of the prophet muhammad (saw), al-tufayl ibn amr al-dawsi (ra), and how he did not listen to the propaganda against islam rather he thought for himself and became a dawah carrier.

the second speaker spoke to the many youth at the event reminding them of the challenging times they live in. the speaker went in detail about the eminent companion and cousin of the prophet muhammad (saw) jafar ibn abi talib (ra). relating his life and especially his time in abyssinia where he (ra) used his wisdom and foresight to give dawah in the highest court of the najashi king, never compromising his stance but using wisdom to win any arguments thrown at him (ra) by his foes. the speaker concluded with saying the youth have to learn the arguments and ideas and study islam to go forward like jafar (ra) in giving dawah to muslims and the wider community at large.

the event ended with a lively q&a and with food and interaction.

#islam #confidence #standfornothingfallforanything

text:
happy 2019!

as you set your intentions for the new year, i offer up the radical notion of being okay with others not being okay with you. weâ€™ve heard the research about how women who are ambitious or negotiate salaries are unlikable. but the flip side â€” that only women who are obedient are likable â€” is a trap. staying small so that others can stay small-minded sucks. i know. i did it for many years. what if, instead, we all got comfortable with ruffling a few feathers, enduring some awkward silences and stares, and speaking our truths? imagine that. 
#leadership #women #speakingout #metoo #timesup #resolutions #2019

text:
mgtow 101: principles and accountability

when i debate people i like to focus on the common principle. by common principle i mean the overall answer that stays consistent, if you swap out the subject, verb or noun.

using this scenario as an example, whenÂ people say, "if he didn't want the baby, he should have worn a condom", i say, "what if that same man gave you and the baby hiv, as a result of unprotected sex". would you still say, he should have worn a condom, or would you take accountability and see where you fucked up?

the reason why they make this statement is because the child is a reward and not a punishment to most women. they don't view the baby as directly having a negative effect on their quality of life.

they get money, child support, section 8, food stamps, validation as a mother (by society). they also get the right to always be a victim (blaming the father) as well as unconditional love. if it  weren't for kids, many women would never feel true love, since they don't deserve based off their own merit.

the child benefits her with no consequences. the man has the burden and consequences looming over his head, from the moment she says my period is late.

when you throw the hiv scenario into it, it changes the whole game, she won't get love from others, she can't play the victim about how she got it and she won't get rewarded for having hiv. so she is forced to take accountability. the hiv and the baby stem from the same action, unprotected sex. the lack or principles and accountability is the reason why black women lead in std's as well as out of wedlock births.

the principal stays the same regardless of if you are benefitting or not. if your response or answer changes up depending on if you benefit or not, it shows you lack accountability, character and morals. true accountability is to put the blame on your self in every situation, no matter the factors. women that use this statement without acknowledging she chose the man is a basica.

if she should have worn a condom for the hiv she should also make him wear one to prevent the baby.

what could you have done to make the situation better?

what could you have done to prevent this situation?

ğŸ’™have found the strength to purge toxic relationships in work and my personal life
ğŸ’™have had the courage to take my career into my own hands, starting new projects and expressing my abilities creatively
ğŸ’™have had the strength to address past childhood trauma head on in the name of healing through intense therapy
ğŸ’™have the most incredible partner one could ask for who supports me in every way and makes me a better human
ğŸ’™be living in the age of the girl! the #metoo movement has not only empowered me to speak up about my past experiences but to also address them and heal from within
ğŸ’™to have so much love surrounding me, z, and v. our community means everything to us. thank you everyone for the support the past year. ğŸ’œlesson of the yearâ¡ï¸to stand up for what you believe in and be true to who you are! ğŸ¤œğŸ½ğŸ¤›ğŸ¿ğŸ™ŒğŸ½
may we all heal and move forward to be the best humans we can be in 2019! blessings to you and yours!

today is the first day our founder, kat gordon, will be sharing daily observations over at @katch_phrases. follow her there and read todayâ€™s post below: 
happy 2019!

as you set your intentions for the new year, i offer up the radical notion of being okay with others not being okay with you. weâ€™ve heard the research about how women who are ambitious or negotiate salaries are unlikable. but the flip side â€” that only women who are obedient are likable â€” is a trap. staying small so that others can stay small-minded sucks. i know. i did it for many years. what if, instead, we all got comfortable with ruffling a few feathers, enduring some awkward silences and stares, and speaking our truths? imagine that. 
#leadership #women #speakingout #metoo #timesup #resolutions #2019

text:
an imperious lesson from 2018 :  b a l a n c e 
beauty and the beast. ram and ravan.  failure and success. best and the worst. there are legendary poets and novelists who have pen down their thoughts on balance of life. infact, life itself teaches us this very important virtue. do you know why, because one cannot partake success if he/she hasnâ€™t tasted failure! cannot endure sweetness, if bitterness is yet to be experienced; and thatâ€™s the jim-dandy of life. if you can once and for all learn to accept and savour the bad and good experiences equally, youâ€™ll start to actually appreciate how your life is at par excellence. 
this is a post from my very own personal experiences, and believe me if i say that 2018 was by far the best year of my life, i literally mean it! just because if iâ€™ve faced the brutally bad times in the past year (#metoo) so have i experienced the most propitious time (#solotravel) as well. the difference i realise in all the other years that have passed and #2018 is the difference of b a l a n c e. you ought to have the two extreme virtues of life in order to make it stupendously alive ! trust me, it works beyond magic and miraculously!
